    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is an Abstract Class?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "An abstract class is a base class that cannot be instantiated directly and may contain abstract methods that must be implemented by subclasses."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Abstract Class Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "abstract class Animal {\n  abstract makeSound(): void;\n\n  move() {\n    console.log('Moving');\n  }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Extending Abstract Class"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "class Dog extends Animal {\n  makeSound() {\n    console.log('Bark');\n  }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Cannot Instantiate"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
